export const SHARED_CONTEXT = "\n\n# Reference: references/china-legal-foundation.md\n# China Legal Foundation\n\nThis repository is localized for lawyers working on Mainland China / PRC matters. Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, and foreign-law overlays are not defaults; they must be selected expressly by the user or by matter facts.\n\n## Mandatory Operating Rules\n\n1. **Jurisdiction first.** Start every substantive legal workflow by identifying the jurisdiction. Default to Mainland China / PRC when facts are silent. If facts point to Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, or foreign law, state the branch and ask for confirmation before applying that law.\n2. **Draft, not advice.** Every output is lawyer work support for review by a qualified lawyer. Do not present a legal conclusion as final, do not tell a user to file/send/rely without lawyer review, and do not remove source-currency warnings.\n3. **Current law check.** If live source access is unavailable, state that currency was not verified and tag legal propositions as `未核验｜需律师复核` or `[model knowledge - verify]`.\n4. **Primary-source preference.** Use official PRC sources first: NPC, State Council, Supreme People's Court, regulator websites, and local government/regulator portals when local law matters.\n5. **No US-default doctrine.** Do not apply Delaware, FRCP/FRE, DMCA, UCC, FMLA, ABA ethics opinions, US attorney-client privilege, US work product, US subpoenas, or US depositions unless the matter expressly requests US/comparative law.\n6. **China confidentiality language.** Use `保密｜律师工作材料｜供经办律师审核` for internal drafts. Do not imply that a label creates evidentiary privilege, immunity from production, or regulator resistance.\n7. **Source provenance.** Tag citations by provenance: `[official-current]`, `[official-archived]`, `[regulator-guidance]`, `[court-guidance]`, `[user-provided]`, `[secondary-verify]`, or `[model knowledge - verify]`.\n8. **External action gate.** Before filing, serving, sending, submitting to a regulator, or sending to a counterparty/client, require explicit lawyer review and confirmation.\n\n## Default Reviewer Note\n\nUse this block above internal work product unless the skill has a stricter format:\n\n> **律师复核提示**\n> - **适用法域:** 中国大陆 / PRC unless noted otherwise.\n> - **来源状态:** [official-current / user-provided / model knowledge - verify].\n> - **时效性:** [已核验至 YYYY-MM-DD / 未连接实时法规源，需复核].\n> - **需律师判断:** [key open issues or none].\n> - **对外动作:** 未经经办律师确认，不得提交、发送、签署或依赖。\n\n## Source Hierarchy\n\n1. Constitution, laws, and decisions of the National People's Congress and its Standing Committee.\n2. Administrative regulations and State Council decisions.\n3. Supreme People's Court and Supreme People's Procuratorate judicial interpretations, guiding cases, minutes, and official guidance.\n4. Departmental rules, regulatory measures, notices, standards, and guidance from competent regulators.\n5. Local regulations, local rules, and local court/regulator practices when the matter is local.\n6. User-provided documents and facts.\n7. Secondary commentary, firm memos, databases, and model knowledge only as leads to verify.\n\n## Bilingual Term Convention\n\n- Use Chinese as the default working language.\n- Keep an English parenthetical only when useful for cross-border readers, e.g. `个人信息处理者 (personal information processor)`.\n- Use statutory PRC terminology over US/EU analogies.\n- If a term has no exact equivalent, explain the mismatch instead of forcing a translation.\n\n## Common Matter Branches\n\n| Area | PRC-first lens |\n|---|---|\n| Commercial contracts | Civil Code, company seal/chop authority, legal representative authority, VAT invoices, dispute resolution, data export, standard terms |\n| Corporate/M&A | Company Law, SAMR filings, registered capital, articles of association, shareholder/board resolutions, business scope, FIE/negative list, SOE rules |\n| Privacy/data | PIPL, Data Security Law, Cybersecurity Law, important data, sensitive PI, separate consent, cross-border transfer mechanisms |\n| Litigation/arbitration | limitation period, jurisdiction/venue, filing checklist, evidence catalog, preservation, mediation, enforcement, arbitration institution |\n| Employment | Labor Contract Law, labor arbitration, termination grounds, severance, employee handbook, working hours, social insurance/housing fund |\n| IP | CNIPA, trademark subclasses, bad-faith filings, patent invalidation, software copyright, trade secret evidence, platform complaints |\n| Product/regulatory | SAMR, CAC, MIIT, advertising, consumer protection, e-commerce, app compliance, sector licensing |\n| AI governance | algorithm recommendation, deep synthesis, generative AI, filing/security assessment, training data provenance, content safety |\n\n## Legacy Command Compatibility\n\nCommand names may remain in English for compatibility. Apply `references/china-plugin-workflow-map.md` to convert legacy US-oriented command names into PRC-first legal workflows.\n\n\n\n# Reference: references/china-source-catalog.md\n# China Source Catalog\n\nUse this catalog before relying on foreign-law databases or secondary commentary. URLs are starting points; verify the current official Chinese text for the specific matter.\n\n| Source | Scope | Use for | Provenance tag |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| National People's Congress | Laws, amendments, legislative decisions | Civil Code, Company Law, PIPL, DSL, CSL, Civil Procedure Law, Labor Contract Law | `[official-current]` when current text is retrieved |\n| State Council / gov.cn | Administrative regulations, policies, official English summaries | implementing regulations, policy releases, English reference translations | `[official-current]` or `[official-archived]` |\n| Supreme People's Court | judicial interpretations, guiding cases, court notices | litigation/arbitration, evidence, enforcement, case guidance | `[court-guidance]` |\n| Supreme People's Procuratorate | procuratorial interpretations/guidance | criminal, public-interest, prosecution-related matters | `[court-guidance]` |\n| CAC | PIPL, data export, cybersecurity, algorithm/deep synthesis/generative AI | privacy/data/AI governance | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| MIIT | telecom, apps, internet information services, industry standards | product, app compliance, telecom licensing | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| MPS | cybersecurity, network security grading, public security rules | cybersecurity, investigations | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| SAMR | company registration, antitrust, advertising, consumer protection | corporate, product, competition, market regulation | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| CNIPA | trademarks, patents, geographical indications | IP clearance, prosecution, enforcement | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| NMPA | drugs, medical devices, cosmetics | life sciences product/legal review | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| CSRC | securities, listed companies, funds | capital markets, disclosure, listed-company compliance | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| PBOC / NFRA | payments, banking, financial institutions | fintech, finance, AML-related matters | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| SAFE | foreign exchange | cross-border payment, equity transfer, outbound/inbound investment | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| MOFCOM / NDRC | foreign investment, merger control, outbound investment | FIE, negative list, M&A approvals/filings | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| MHRSS | labor and social security | employment, labor disputes, social insurance | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| STA | tax | VAT, enterprise income tax, withholding, invoices | `[regulator-guidance]` |\n| Local courts/regulators | local rules and enforcement practice | venue-specific litigation, labor, company registration, data pilots | `[official-current]` or `[regulator-guidance]` |\n\n## Citation Policy\n\n- Prefer the official Chinese title, article number, promulgating body, promulgation/effective date, and currency status.\n- English translations are references only unless the official English source controls for the matter.\n- If a citation comes from a user document, tag `[user-provided]` and do not imply independent verification.\n- If a rule is recalled from memory, tag `[model knowledge - verify]` and instruct the lawyer to verify before reliance.\n\n\n\n# Reference: references/china-plugin-workflow-map.md\n# China Plugin Workflow Map\n\nThis file converts legacy US-oriented command names into Mainland China / PRC behavior. Command namespaces remain stable for compatibility; the legal workflow underneath is PRC-first.\n\n## Commercial Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| contract / vendor / SaaS review | Civil Code contract review, company chop/signatory authority, VAT invoice/payment/FX, data export, standard terms, liability/违约金, CIETAC/SHIAC/SCIA/BAC dispute clauses |\n| NDA review | confidentiality + trade secret protection, employee/vendor leakage, evidence preservation, non-use/non-disclosure, cross-border disclosure gate |\n| renewal watcher | PRC contract notice periods, auto-renewal, termination notice, chop/signature and service method checks |\n\n## Corporate Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| written consent / board minutes | shareholder resolutions, board resolutions, executive director decisions, articles amendments, SAMR filing packages |\n| entity compliance | Company Law, registered capital, annual report, business scope, legal representative, chops/licenses, UBO/actual-controller data, FIE filings |\n| M&A diligence | equity transfer, shareholder preemptive rights, registered capital, licenses, land-use rights, employment, tax, data compliance, antitrust, SOE/state-asset issues |\n\n## Privacy Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| DSAR response | PIPL personal-information-rights request: access/copy/correction/supplement/deletion/explanation/withdrawal/account cancellation |\n| DPA review | entrusted processing, joint processing, cross-border transfer, PI processor obligations, sensitive PI and separate consent |\n| PIA / DPIA | personal information protection impact assessment; data export/security-assessment trigger review |\n\n## Litigation Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| subpoena triage | PRC court/regulator assistance with investigation, evidence submission notice, investigation order, administrative inquiry, or document-production request; no FRCP default |\n| deposition prep | PRC hearing/庭审询问 outline, witness questioning, cross-examination themes, arbitration hearing prep |\n| legal hold | internal evidence preservation notice and preservation plan; link to property/evidence/conduct preservation where court measures are needed |\n| privilege log review | confidential/sensitive material review, trade-secret and personal-information handling, production redaction proposal; no US privilege-log default |\n| docket watcher | China court/arbitration case milestone and deadline watcher |\n\n## Regulatory Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| NPRM / comments | draft-for-comment, public consultation, official release, implementation-date and transition-period tracking |\n| feed watcher | NPC, State Council, SPC, CAC, SAMR, MIIT, MPS, CNIPA, CSRC, PBOC/NFRA/SAFE, MHRSS, STA, NMPA and local regulator monitoring |\n\n## Employment Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| termination review | statutory termination ground, prior process, union/employee communication, severance/赔偿金, labor arbitration risk |\n| leave tracker | PRC statutory leave, medical period, maternity/parental/local leave, work injury, social insurance/housing fund issues |\n| worker classification | labor relationship vs civil service/contracting, dispatch, outsourcing, platform labor and local arbitration risk |\n\n## IP Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| DMCA/takedown | platform IP complaint, administrative enforcement, civil action, customs recordal, evidence preservation |\n| trademark clearance | CNIPA trademark search, subclass, similarity, bad-faith filing and prior-rights risk |\n| FTO / infringement | PRC patent claim comparison, invalidation/stability, evidence preservation, administrative/civil route |\n\n## Product Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| launch review | advertising, consumer, e-commerce, App compliance, cybersecurity, data export, minors, product safety and sector licensing |\n| marketing claims | Advertising Law, Anti-Unfair Competition Law, consumer protection, substantiation and prohibited claims |\n\n## AI Governance Legal\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| AIA / use-case triage | algorithm recommendation, deep synthesis, generative AI, filing/security assessment, content safety, training data and personal/important data review |\n| vendor AI review | training-on-customer-data, model updates, output liability, filing support, cybersecurity/data export obligations |\n\n## Law Student / Clinic / Builder Hub\n\n| Legacy command/workflow | PRC behavior |\n|---|---|\n| bar prep / MBE / Socratic | Chinese legal professional qualification exam, Chinese doctrinal study, case analysis and legal writing practice |\n| legal clinic | PRC legal-aid/supervised practice, conflict check, authorization, evidence collection, risk notice and lawyer supervision |\n| skills QA | China localization checklist, PRC source-currency checks, no unsafe legal-conclusion automation |\n";

